-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This are the Dockerfiles used for building / cross-compiling sigrok, pulseview,
smuview, etc. and their dependencies inside docker containers.
Also used for CI/CD with github actions.


Status
------

In development


Requirements
------------

- docker


Available Dockerfiles
---------------------

Dockerfile.sigrok-mxe:

  This image conatins everything that is needed to cross compile pulseview,
  smuview and sigrok-cli for Windows (>= XP).
  Available targets are i686-w64-mingw32.static.posix and x86_64-w64-mingw32.static.posix

  ToDo:
  Prop. needed?: pkg-config
  Removed: cmake, nsis, scons, sdcc
  Added: doxygen (Dependency for libsigrok C++, not available for MXE but host doxygen will be OK... Urgs!)


Building
--------

 $ docker build -t -f
